@node Problems "Problems with SWOS Ed"

  @{b}@{u}Common problems@{uu}@{ub}

  Q: What is MUI and why can't I run SWOS Ed without it?

  A: MUI is a system to generate good looking, font sensitive and easy to use
     graphical user interfaces.  I think that every Amigan should use it!  
     You can download util/libs/mui38usr.lha from Aminet.  For a more
     detailed description of MUI, see the @{"MUI" LINK MUI} section of this guide.


  Q: I have the floppy version of SWOS.  How can I install it on a HD?  My
     problem is that when I try to save an unpacked data file produced by 
     SWOS Ed, the disk is too full.

  A: Just install ProPack Clone and repack data files.  This should solve
     all problems. But if there is a reason that you don't want to do it,
     you can also solve the problem as follows.

     My SWOS HD installer should be available on Aminet as swoshd.lha in
     game/patch.  If you don't have a hard  disk  (why not ???) you could  
     make enough room by deleting the following files from SWOS disk 2:  

     TEAM.080, TEAM.081, TEAM.082, TEAM.083, TEAM.084, TEAM.085.  

     These files contain the international data, so if you delete them you
     won't be able to play the world cup for example.


  Q: When I try to edit the English teams or I update POOLPLYR.DAT file it
     makes SWOS crash. What can I do to get around this?

  A: The English league data file is the largest and when it's unpacked it's
     about three times bigger!  That's the reason that the game crashes.  The 
     unpacked file is larger than SWOS's internal buffer and the game can't 
     load it properly.  The same problem occurs with POOLPLYR.DAT file. To make
     the game work properly, you have to repack the file using an external packer
     program like ProPack or ProPack Clone.  Everything will then work fine.


  Q: What can I do to encourage the author to write updated versions of SWOS Ed?

  A: It's very simple.  First of all register, then send him a nice postcard,
     suggestions, accelerator boards for his A1200, millions of dollars,
     a few expensive cars etc.


  Please also read @{"Important" LINK Important} section of this guide.

  If you still don't know how to fix your problem, visit my WWW
  home page (see @{"Author" LINK Author}).  If you still can't find a solution,
  please e-mail me.
  
@endnode

