@node PPClone "ProPack Clone and its author"

  @{b}@{u}What is ProPack Clone?@{uu}@{ub}

ProPack Clone (PPClone) is a program that can compress files in a format
compatable with ProPack, a compressor written by Rob Northern Computing. This
packer was used on many commercial games for a number of years, SWOS being
one of the last.

Since the last version was dated 1993 and there does not seem to be a legal
way to obtain this program any more, I decided to write my own clone of it. I
did this for the sole purpose of letting people edit their SWOS data files,
as I know many people (my self included) regard this game as the best
football simulation ever and it is a shame not to have the latest teams for
it.

Therefore, I decided that I should release PPClone with Piotr Bieniek as part
of this exellent SWOS Ed package.

Please note that I am in no way trying to make any finantial gain from
PPClone, nor do I wish it be used for any purpose other than compressing SWOS
data files. There are much better packers in the public domain these days, so
there should be no reason to use PPClone for anything else.

  @{b}@{u}Copyright notice@{uu}@{ub}

PPClone is (C) 1999 Paul Qureshi. It is free, but may only be distributed
with the complete SWOS Ed package by Piotr Bieniek. It may only be used
for compressing edited data files for use with an original (not pirated)
version of SWOS.

Piotr and I take no responsability for anything this program might do,
harmful or otherwise. However, it should work without problems.

